  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/859686404" />
    <a title="Eric Michael" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16983768-eric-michael"><img alt="Eric Michael" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1391034945p2/16983768.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/859686404?book_show_action=true">Feb 19, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eric Michael" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eric Michael" href="/user/show/16983768-eric-michael">Eric Michael</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer859686404" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6861204153273695911">I found The Meat Market to be a breath of fresh air, when compared to most of the other books that I have read lately. Chalk definitely writes in his own unique tone, which creates vivid scenes and characters in this book. The main character Harkon is a complex and engaging dude, and while I was never quite sure if I entirely liked him, couldn&apos;t help but root for him in this seedy sci-fi world.<br/><br/>This book is an excellent change-up if you are looking for a book that will get you thinking and take y</span>
  <span id="freeText6861204153273695911" style="display:none">I found The Meat Market to be a breath of fresh air, when compared to most of the other books that I have read lately. Chalk definitely writes in his own unique tone, which creates vivid scenes and characters in this book. The main character Harkon is a complex and engaging dude, and while I was never quite sure if I entirely liked him, couldn't help but root for him in this seedy sci-fi world.<br /><br />This book is an excellent change-up if you are looking for a book that will get you thinking and take you down a road that you will think about for a while (perhaps with trepidation). Highly Recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6861204153273695911" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


